The global textile flame retardants market is expected to witness significant growth by 2028, driven by increasing concerns regarding fire safety regulations in the textile industry. In terms of type, the market is segmented into inorganic flame retardants and organic flame retardants. Inorganic flame retardants are commonly used due to their effectiveness in reducing flammability. Organic flame retardants are also gaining traction as they offer environmentally friendly solutions. Based on application, the market is categorized into apparel, home textiles, industrial textiles, and others. The apparel segment is expected to dominate the market due to the rising demand for flame-retardant clothing across various end-user industries.

